### Worker Resilience Testing
### Archivo HTTP para probar la resiliencia del sistema de workers

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9..aI-c5TSlMrt3UME0n780DRQ4CF_dMXjAL_--LIaP0vU

###############################################
# 1. Verificar información del worker actual
###############################################

### Get Worker Info
GET {{baseUrl}}/test/worker-info
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###############################################
# 2. Health Check
###############################################

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/test/health
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###############################################
# 3. Matar Worker - Muerte Limpia (process.exit)
###############################################

### Kill Worker - Exit (recomendado para primer test)
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/kill-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "exit",
  "delay": 1000
}

###############################################
# 4. Matar Worker - Error No Manejado
###############################################

### Kill Worker - Uncaught Exception
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/kill-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "uncaughtException",
  "delay": 500
}

###############################################
# 5. Matar Worker - Promesa Rechazada
###############################################

### Kill Worker - Async Error
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/kill-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "asyncError",
  "delay": 500
}

###############################################
# 6. Matar Worker - Loop Infinito (CUIDADO!)
###############################################

### Kill Worker - Infinite Loop (bloqueará el worker)
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/kill-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "infiniteLoop",
  "delay": 1000
}

###############################################
# 7. Matar Worker - Memory Leak (CUIDADO!)
###############################################

### Kill Worker - Memory Leak (matará el proceso eventualmente)
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/kill-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "memoryLeak",
  "delay": 1000
}

###############################################
# 8. Stress Test - Carga CPU
###############################################

### Stress Worker - Low Intensity
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/stress-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "duration": 5000,
  "intensity": "low"
}

### Stress Worker - Medium Intensity
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/stress-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "duration": 5000,
  "intensity": "medium"
}

### Stress Worker - High Intensity (puede bloquear el worker temporalmente)
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/stress-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "duration": 3000,
  "intensity": "high"
}

###############################################
# 9. Test Secuencial - Verificar Recuperación
###############################################

### Paso 1: Get worker info (anotar PID)
GET {{baseUrl}}/test/worker-info
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Paso 2: Matar worker
POST {{baseUrl}}/test/kill-worker
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "method": "exit",
  "delay": 1000
}

### Paso 3: Esperar 3 segundos y verificar nuevo worker (PID diferente)
GET {{baseUrl}}/test/worker-info
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### Paso 4: Verificar que la API sigue funcionando
GET {{baseUrl}}/dashboard/actividad-reciente
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###############################################
# GUÍA DE USO
###############################################

# 1. Modo Single Process (USE_CLUSTER=false):
#    - No habrá restart automático
#    - El servidor se caerá completamente
#    - Útil para testing de errores

# 2. Modo Cluster (USE_CLUSTER=true):
#    - El master detectará la muerte del worker
#    - Creará un nuevo worker automáticamente
#    - El servicio seguirá disponible
#    - Verás en logs: "💀 Worker XXX died... Restarting..."

# RECOMENDACIONES:
# - Empezar con method=exit y delay=1000
# - Verificar PID antes y después
# - No usar infiniteLoop o memoryLeak en producción
# - Los métodos más seguros son: exit, uncaughtException, asyncError

# QUÉ OBSERVAR:
# 1. En logs del servidor:
#    - "💀 Worker XXX died (1). Restarting..."
#    - "👷 New worker YYY started as replacement"
# 2. La API debe seguir respondiendo
# 3. El PID del worker cambiará después del restart
